Direct Known Subclasses:
BigDecimalParameterExpression, BigIntegerParameterExpression, BooleanParameterExpression, IntegerParameterExpression, StringParameterExpression, TimestampParameterExpression
public abstract class AbstractSingleParameterExpression<P>
extends Expression
implements ISingleParameterExpression<P>

An abstract implementation of the basic methods of the single parameter expression interface, which is suitable for expressions in a WHERE or FROM clause that have a single parameter, or for expressions that constitute a parameter by itself (expression "?", in other words). The concrete implementations specify the data type P and implement the bind() method with the appropriate JDBC code necessary for that data type.

Author:
Robert J. Muller
